p: Digested kenaf ( Hibiscus cannabinus L.) seed O/W NEs stabilized by a SCas, Tween 20, and Î²-CD complex demonstrated good lipid digestion, significant bioaccessibility of antioxidants (tocopherols and total phenolic contents), and lower phytosterol degradation rate compared to digested bulk oil, which indicates the possibility of their future application in food and nutraceutical industries [ 164].
